  <h1><strong>King Gizzard &amp; the Lizard Wizard</strong></h1>
  <p>
    <img
      src="https://picsum.photos/seed/king-gizzard/1280/720"
      alt="King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard"
      title="King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard"
    />
  </p>
  <p>
    King Gizzard &amp; the Lizard Wizard are an Australian rock band formed in <a
      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melbourne"
      title="Melbourne">Melbourne</a
    > in 2010. The seven-piece, fronted by Stu Mackenzie, is known for restlessly
    hopping between genres — garage rock, microtonal metal, jazz fusion, synth-pop
    and folk all feature across its catalogue.
  </p>
  <hr />
  <p>
    The band has released over twenty studio albums, most notably <em
      ><a
        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonagon_Infinity"
        title="Nonagon Infinity">Nonagon Infinity</a
      ></em
    > (2016), a continuous loop where the final track leads back into the first.
    In 2017 they released five albums in a single year, and in 2022 they followed
    up with another five — including three released simultaneously on the same
    day.
  </p>
</DocLayout>
